## 𝐇𝐨𝐰 𝐭𝐨 𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐞

1. Create a folder called videos in the same place where you’ll save the script.
2. Put all your .mp4 video files inside that videos folder.
3. Save the Python script below as generate_youtube_clone.py.
4. Run the script to generate index.html.
5. Open index.html in your web browser.


## 𝐇𝐨𝐰 𝐭𝐨 𝐑𝐮𝐧 (Quick Steps ik most of you know but still) 

1. Make sure you have Python installed.
2. Put your .mp4 video files inside a folder called videos (in the same directory as the script).
3. Save the above code as generate_youtube_clone.py.
4. Open terminal or command prompt in that folder.
Run:
python generate_youtube_clone.py
5. Open the generated index.html in any modern browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge).
6. Use the search bar to filter videos.
7. Click Toggle Dark Mode button to switch light/dark theme.


## 𝐓𝐫𝐨𝐮𝐛𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐓𝐢𝐩𝐬

* If python command not found, try python3 instead.
* Videos must be .mp4 format.
* Video filenames become their titles automatically.
*** To add/remove videos, just update the videos folder and run the script again or type cmd in the folder path and pest "python generate_youtube_clone.py" hit enter and you are good to go again. After adding new videos you have to update the script or the new videos will not be foud in page. 
